CCGBI + GTT MATHEMATICAL FRAMEWORK
Complete ROI Model for Environmental Restoration & AI-Era Employment

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

DOCUMENT PURPOSE

This framework translates the Lighthouse Resilience Program measurement methodology to civilization-scale transformation through:

1. CCGBI (Crayon Colored Global Basic Income) - Environmental restoration employment
2. GTT (Global Telephone Tag) - AI integration for human flourishing

The mathematics demonstrate measurable return on investment across:
- Environmental restoration
- Economic transformation
- Neurochemical healing
- AI-proof employment creation
- Institutional partnership success
- Generational acceleration

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

PART 1: THE CORE VARIABLES

A. COST VARIABLES (Per Community, Per Year)

E = Environmental Degradation Cost
   Definition: Annual cost of environmental damage and remediation liability
   Components:
   - Toxic site cleanup liability
   - Waterway contamination health impacts
   - Lost ecosystem services (clean water, biodiversity, soil fertility)
   - Future remediation obligations
   
   Measurement:
   - Government environmental assessments
   - Health department contamination-related illness costs
   - Ecosystem service valuation studies
   - Projected cleanup liabilities

U = Unemployment & Welfare Cost
   Definition: Annual cost of unemployment and associated support
   Components:
   - Direct welfare payments
   - Unemployment insurance
   - Lost productivity (capable people unemployed)
   - Mental health impacts of purposelessness
   
   Measurement:
   - Government welfare expenditures per community
   - Unemployment rate × average support cost
   - Healthcare costs for unemployment-related depression/addiction
   - Estimated lost economic productivity

T = Trauma & Health Cost
   Definition: Annual cost of intergenerational trauma and stress-related illness
   Components:
   - Mental health treatment (addiction, PTSD, depression, anxiety)
   - Physical health (stress-related disease: cardiovascular, diabetes, immune)
   - Intergenerational transmission (children affected by parent trauma)
   - Crisis intervention and emergency services
   
   Measurement:
   - Community mental health service costs
   - Addiction treatment expenditures
   - Stress-related physical health costs
   - Child welfare intervention costs

A = AI Displacement Cost (Projected)
   Definition: Future annual cost of AI-driven job elimination
   Components:
   - Jobs eliminated by automation
   - Retraining that becomes obsolete
   - Social instability from mass unemployment
   - Lost tax revenue from eliminated positions
   
   Measurement:
   - McKinsey/PwC AI displacement projections for region
   - Current job types × automation probability
   - Retraining program costs with limited effectiveness
   - Estimated social support for displaced workers

I = Institutional Breakdown Cost
   Definition: Annual cost of failed programs and trust deficit
   Components:
   - Ineffective reconciliation programs (symbolic, no impact)
   - Repeated intervention failures
   - Trust deficit preventing community engagement
   - Burnout of systems and workers
   
   Measurement:
   - Budget for programs with documented low impact
   - Administrative overhead of failed initiatives
   - Cost of community disengagement (missed opportunities)
   - Worker turnover in helping professions

n = Number of Community Members/Participants
   Definition: Size of affected population
   
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

B. INTERVENTION IMPACT VARIABLES (Post-CCGBI + GTT)

E′ = Environmental Cost After CCGBI
   Formula: E′ = E × (1 − %Environmental_Restoration)
   
   Where %Environmental_Restoration is measured by:
   - Water quality improvement (contaminant reduction %)
   - Waste removed (tons collected and processed)
   - Biodiversity recovery (species counts, habitat health)
   - Soil quality improvement (testing results)
   - Ecosystem services restored (clean water production, carbon sequestration)

U′ = Unemployment Cost After CCGBI
   Formula: U′ = U × (1 − %Employment_Increase)
   
   Where %Employment_Increase is measured by:
   - Participants employed in CCGBI work
   - Income earned through restoration
   - Welfare exits (people no longer requiring support)
   - Small businesses formed (entrepreneurial tier)
   - Skills gained (Blue/Green/Black/Gold level progression)

T′ = Trauma/Health Cost After CCGBI
   Formula: T′ = T × (1 − %Neurochemical_Improvement)
   
   Where %Neurochemical_Improvement is measured by:
   - PSS (Perceived Stress Scale) reduction
   - ProQOL (Professional Quality of Life) improvement
   - Purpose scales (meaning, contribution, belonging)
   - Addiction recovery rates
   - Physical health indicators (cortisol regulation, cardiovascular health)
   - Self-reported wellbeing increases

A′ = AI Displacement Cost After GTT
   Formula: A′ = A × (1 − %AI_Proof_Work)
   
   Where %AI_Proof_Work is measured by:
   - Jobs created that AI fundamentally cannot do
   - Work requiring physical presence in complex natural environments
   - Work requiring community-based trust and relationships
   - Work requiring ethical judgment in restoration contexts
   - GTT data quality (authentic human needs collected)
   - AI partnership quality (technology amplifying, not replacing)

I′ = Institutional Cost After Partnership Model
   Formula: I′ = I × (1 − %Trust_Restoration)
   
   Where %Trust_Restoration is measured by:
   - Partnership sustainability (months/years operational)
   - Community satisfaction surveys
   - Replication requests from other communities
   - Conflict resolution success rates
   - Shared decision-making quality
   - Authentic reconciliation indicators (not symbolic gestures)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

C. HUMAN VALUE COMPOSITE INDEX

W = R + B + N + V + M + Gᵥ + Fₑ + Fₘ

Each component scored 0-10 (Maximum total = 80 points)

R = Resilience (Neurochemical Health)
   Measured by:
   - Cortisol regulation (stress hormone normalized)
   - Healthy dopamine function (motivation, achievement)
   - Balanced serotonin (mood stability, contentment)
   - Adequate oxytocin (connection, trust, belonging)
   - Endorphin activation (joy, vitality, pain relief)
   
   Instruments:
   - PSS (Perceived Stress Scale)
   - ProQOL subscales
   - Self-reported wellbeing scales
   - Optional: Salivary cortisol testing, HRV (Heart Rate Variability)

B = Belonging (Community Cohesion)
   Measured by:
   - Partnership participation rates
   - Elder-youth connection frequency
   - Peer support network strength
   - Social connectedness scales
   - Community event attendance
   - Mutual aid exchanges
   
   Instruments:
   - Social connectedness scales
   - Partnership longevity tracking
   - Community cohesion surveys
   - Relationship quality assessments

N = Neurochemical Optimization
   Measured by:
   - Dopamine: Achievement through color progression
   - Serotonin: Meaning through contribution recognition
   - Oxytocin: Connection through shared sacred work
   - Endorphins: Joy through embodied outdoor activity
   
   Instruments:
   - Validated neurochemical proxy scales
   - Mood and affect inventories
   - Vitality and energy scores
   - Flow state frequency

V = Vocational Purpose
   Measured by:
   - Meaningful work engagement
   - Skill progression (White→Blue→Green→Black→Gold)
   - Contribution recognition
   - Mastery achievement
   - Career pathway clarity
   
   Instruments:
   - Purpose in Life scales
   - Work meaning inventories
   - Skill progression tracking
   - Achievement documentation

M = Meaning-Making
   Measured by:
   - Legacy creation activities
   - Seven-generations thinking
   - Sacred work engagement
   - Existential fulfillment
   - Generativity (concern for future generations)
   
   Instruments:
   - Existential fulfillment scales
   - Generativity assessments
   - Legacy project documentation
   - Meaning in Life questionnaires

Gᵥ = Generational Value Transfer
   Measured by:
   - Elder wisdom transmission (hours teaching)
   - Youth skill development (competencies gained)
   - Attachment security (children's relationship quality)
   - Traditional knowledge preservation
   - Intergenerational program participation
   
   Instruments:
   - Elder teaching logs
   - Youth engagement tracking
   - Attachment security assessments (children)
   - Knowledge transmission documentation

Fₑ = Environmental Flourishing
   Measured by:
   - Land healing (hectares restored)
   - Species recovery (biodiversity counts)
   - Ecosystem restoration (water quality, soil health)
   - Visible transformation (before/after documentation)
   
   Instruments:
   - Environmental quality testing
   - Biodiversity surveys
   - Ecosystem health assessments
   - Photo/video documentation

Fₘ = Future Momentum
   Measured by:
   - Next generation starting from higher baseline
   - Children's cortisol levels (lower than previous generation)
   - Secure attachment rates (children)
   - Purpose formation in youth
   - Reduced intergenerational trauma transmission
   
   Instruments:
   - Longitudinal child development tracking
   - Baseline comparison across generations
   - Trauma transmission indicators
   - Youth thriving assessments

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

PART 2: THE CORE FORMULAS

FORMULA 1: CURRENT STATE COST (Baseline)

Current Cost = (E + U + T + A + I) × n

Where:
E = Environmental degradation annual cost
U = Unemployment/welfare annual cost
T = Trauma/health annual cost
A = AI displacement projected annual cost
I = Institutional breakdown annual cost
n = Community size (typically = 1 for per-community calculations)

This represents total annual cost of dysfunction without CCGBI + GTT intervention.

---

FORMULA 2: POST-INTERVENTION COST

Projected Cost = (E′ + U′ + T′ + A′ + I′) × n

Where:
E′ = E × (1 − %Environmental_Restoration)
U′ = U × (1 − %Employment_Increase)
T′ = T × (1 − %Neurochemical_Improvement)
A′ = A × (1 − %AI_Proof_Work)
I′ = I × (1 − %Trust_Restoration)

This represents total annual cost after CCGBI + GTT implementation,
accounting for measurable improvements in each domain.

---

FORMULA 3: ANNUAL COST SAVINGS

ΔCost = Current Cost − Projected Cost

This represents direct annual financial savings from intervention.

---

FORMULA 4: HUMAN VALUE INCREASE

W = R + B + N + V + M + Gᵥ + Fₑ + Fₘ

Where each component scores 0-10 points (Maximum = 80 points total)

This represents qualitative improvement in human flourishing,
which can be monetized using context-appropriate value per point.

---

FORMULA 5: MULTIPLIER EFFECTS

Gₘ = Entrepreneurial Value + Equipment Activation + Ripple Benefits

Components:
- Small businesses formed (participants becoming owners)
- Idle equipment activated (boats, trucks, machinery earning income)
- Tourism and media value (communities showing transformation)
- Knowledge transfer (other communities learning from success)
- Innovation emergence (participants improving methodologies)

This represents additional value beyond direct cost savings.

---

FORMULA 6: TOTAL ANNUAL IMPACT

Total Impact = ΔCost + (W × Value_Multiplier) + Gₘ

Where:
ΔCost = Annual cost savings
W = Human Value composite score
Value_Multiplier = Dollar value per Human Value point (context-dependent)
Gₘ = Multiplier effects

This represents complete first-year value creation.

---

FORMULA 7: MULTI-YEAR PROJECTION

Future Value (Y years) = (ΔCost × Y) + (W × Y × Growth_Factor^Y) + (ΔCost × SRF)

Where:
Y = Number of years projected
Growth_Factor = Annual improvement rate as system matures (typically 1.05-1.15)
SRF = Systemic Ripple Factor (value from other communities adopting model)

Typical SRF values:
- Conservative: 2 (model replicates to 1-2 other communities)
- Moderate: 5 (model replicates to 4-5 other communities)
- Optimistic: 10 (model replicates to 9-10 other communities)

---

FORMULA 8: GENERATIONAL ACCELERATION

Generational Impact = Gen₁ + (Gen₂ × 1.5) + (Gen₃ × 2.5)

Where:
Gen₁ = Value from current generation (25 years)
Gen₂ = Value from second generation starting from healthier baseline (1.5× multiplier)
Gen₃ = Value from third generation starting from thriving baseline (2.5× multiplier)

Rationale for multipliers:
- Gen 2 starts with: reduced trauma, secure attachment, purpose from childhood (50% advantage)
- Gen 3 starts with: two generations of healing, consciousness evolution (150% advantage)

This represents 75-100 year transformation value.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

PART 3: WORKED EXAMPLE (CONSERVATIVE ESTIMATES)

SCENARIO: First Nations Community, Population 500

---

STEP 1: ESTABLISH BASELINE COSTS (Current State)

E = Environmental Degradation Cost = $500,000/year
   Breakdown:
   - Water contamination health impacts: $200,000
   - Lost ecosystem services: $150,000
   - Future remediation liability: $100,000
   - Toxic site monitoring: $50,000

U = Unemployment & Welfare Cost = $300,000/year
   Breakdown:
   - 100 unemployed adults × $2,000/month support = $240,000
   - Lost productivity (estimated): $40,000
   - Mental health from purposelessness: $20,000

T = Trauma & Health Cost = $400,000/year
   Breakdown:
   - Mental health services (addiction, PTSD, depression): $200,000
   - Stress-related physical illness: $120,000
   - Intergenerational trauma impacts: $50,000
   - Crisis intervention: $30,000

A = AI Displacement Cost (Projected) = $200,000/year
   Breakdown:
   - 50 jobs at risk × $3,000/year projected impact = $150,000
   - Retraining costs with limited effectiveness: $30,000
   - Social instability impacts: $20,000

I = Institutional Breakdown Cost = $150,000/year
   Breakdown:
   - Failed reconciliation programs (symbolic): $80,000
   - Administrative overhead of ineffective initiatives: $40,000
   - Community disengagement opportunity cost: $20,000
   - Worker burnout and turnover: $10,000

n = 1 (calculating per-community)

Current Cost = ($500,000 + $300,000 + $400,000 + $200,000 + $150,000) × 1
Current Cost = $1,550,000 per year

---

STEP 2: PROJECT POST-INTERVENTION COSTS (After 12 Months CCGBI + GTT)

Conservative Improvement Estimates:

Environmental Restoration: 30% improvement
- Evidence: Water quality testing, waste tonnage removed, biodiversity counts
- E′ = $500,000 × (1 − 0.30) = $350,000

Employment Increase: 40% improvement
- Evidence: 200 participants employed, income earned, welfare exits
- U′ = $300,000 × (1 − 0.40) = $180,000

Neurochemical Improvement: 25% improvement
- Evidence: PSS reduction, ProQOL increase, purpose scales improvement
- T′ = $400,000 × (1 − 0.25) = $300,000

AI-Proof Work: 50% protection
- Evidence: Jobs created that AI cannot do (physical restoration, community trust, ethical judgment)
- A′ = $200,000 × (1 − 0.50) = $100,000

Trust Restoration: 35% improvement
- Evidence: Partnership sustainability, community satisfaction, authentic reconciliation
- I′ = $150,000 × (1 − 0.35) = $97,500

Projected Cost = ($350,000 + $180,000 + $300,000 + $100,000 + $97,500) × 1
Projected Cost = $1,027,500 per year

---

STEP 3: CALCULATE ANNUAL SAVINGS

ΔCost = Current Cost − Projected Cost
ΔCost = $1,550,000 − $1,027,500
ΔCost = $522,500 per year

Direct annual savings: $522,500

---

STEP 4: CALCULATE HUMAN VALUE INCREASE

Scoring each component 0-10 after 12 months CCGBI + GTT:

R (Resilience) = 7
- Cortisol regulated, stress significantly reduced, healthy neurochemical function emerging

B (Belonging) = 8
- Strong partnership forming, peer support networks active, community cohesion high

N (Neurochemicals) = 7
- Healthy dopamine (achievement), oxytocin (connection), serotonin (meaning) activated

V (Vocation) = 8
- Meaningful work daily, clear progression pathway (color levels), contribution recognized

M (Meaning) = 7
- Legacy creation begun, seven-generations thinking emerging, sacred work engaged

Gᵥ (Generational) = 6
- Elder teaching activated (200+ hours), youth engaged (100+ participants), attachment improving

Fₑ (Environmental) = 7
- Land healing visible (50 hectares restored), water quality improved (30%), biodiversity recovering

Fₘ (Future) = 6
- Next generation baseline improving (children's cortisol lower, attachment more secure)

W = 7 + 8 + 7 + 8 + 7 + 6 + 7 + 6 = 56 points (70% of maximum 80)

Monetizing Human Value (Conservative):
Value_Multiplier = $10,000 per point
W × Value_Multiplier = 56 × $10,000 = $560,000

---

STEP 5: CALCULATE MULTIPLIER EFFECTS

Gₘ = Entrepreneurial + Equipment + Ripple

Entrepreneurial Value:
- 10 small businesses formed (participants scaling to entrepreneurial tier)
- Average value: $5,000/business/year = $50,000

Equipment Activation:
- 5 boats previously idle, now earning $8,000/year = $40,000
- 3 trucks previously idle, now earning $12,000/year = $36,000
- Total: $76,000

Ripple Benefits:
- Media coverage and community visibility: $10,000
- Knowledge transfer to 2 other communities considering adoption: $10,000
- Innovation improvements (participants refining methods): $4,000
- Total: $24,000

Gₘ = $50,000 + $76,000 + $24,000 = $150,000

---

STEP 6: TOTAL FIRST-YEAR IMPACT

Total Impact = ΔCost + (W × Value_Multiplier) + Gₘ
Total Impact = $522,500 + $560,000 + $150,000
Total Impact = $1,232,500 first-year value

Return on Investment (if funded at $500,000):
ROI = ($1,232,500 / $500,000) = 2.47
Every dollar invested returns $2.47 in first year

---

STEP 7: 10-YEAR PROJECTION

Using Formula 7 with conservative assumptions:
Y = 10 years
Growth_Factor = 1.08 (8% annual improvement as system matures)
SRF = 3 (conservative - model replicates to 2-3 other communities)

Base Savings:
ΔCost × Y = $522,500 × 10 = $5,225,000

Human Value (with compounding):
W × Y × avg(Growth_Factor) = $560,000 × 10 × 1.08^5 (midpoint)
= $560,000 × 10 × 1.469 = $8,226,400

Ripple Effects:
ΔCost × SRF = $522,500 × 3 = $1,567,500

10-Year Value = $5,225,000 + $8,226,400 + $1,567,500
10-Year Value = $15,018,900

For single community of 500 people over 10 years.

---

STEP 8: GENERATIONAL IMPACT (75-YEAR PROJECTION)

Using Formula 8:

Gen₁ (Years 1-25): 
Base calculation: $15,018,900 (10 years) × 2.5 = $37,547,250

Gen₂ (Years 26-50):
Starts from healthier baseline (1.5× multiplier)
$37,547,250 × 1.5 = $56,320,875

Gen₃ (Years 51-75):
Starts from thriving baseline (2.5× multiplier)
$37,547,250 × 2.5 = $93,868,125

Total 75-Year Value = $37,547,250 + $56,320,875 + $93,868,125
Total 75-Year Value = $187,736,250

For single community of 500 people over three generations.

Per capita value: $187,736,250 / 500 = $375,472 per person over 75 years

This does not include:
- Reduced intergenerational trauma (incalculable human benefit)
- Extended lifespan potential (health span increase)
- Consciousness evolution (qualitative transformation)
- Planetary environmental restoration (ecosystem service value beyond community)

