PART 8: REFERENCES & METHODOLOGY

This ROI framework adapts the Lighthouse Resilience Program measurement methodology
(developed by Neil Schwab for addiction worker burnout prevention) to civilization-scale
transformation through CCGBI + GTT.

Core measurement principles:
- Measure the state (baseline assessment)
- Train/implement the intervention (CCGBI + GTT)
- Re-measure the state (track changes over time)
- Calculate ROI (financial + human value)
- Project future value (multi-year and generational)

Instrument sources:
- ProQOL: Stamm, B. H. (2010). The Concise ProQOL Manual
- PSS: Cohen, S., Kamarck, T., & Mermelstein, R. (1983). Perceived Stress Scale
- BAT: Schaufeli, W. B., et al. (2020). Burnout Assessment Tool

Neurochemical framework:
- Cortisol regulation through outdoor work and financial security
- Dopamine activation through achievement and color progression
- Serotonin increase through meaning and contribution recognition
- Oxytocin generation through partnership and shared sacred work
- Endorphin activation through physical outdoor activity

Generational acceleration:
- Based on attachment theory (Bowlby), intergenerational trauma research,
  epigenetics, and neuroplasticity literature

AI displacement projections:
- McKinsey Global Institute (2023). The Future of Work
- PwC (2023). AI and Automation Impact Studies

Environmental restoration economics:
- Historical precedent: 1800s sanitation revolution wealth creation
- Ecosystem services valuation (Costanza et al., 2014)

